String Operations in C

>> String Copy: Copies one string into another.
>> Finding Length: Determines the length of a string.
>> Reversing a String: Reverses the order of characters in a string.
>> Checking for Palindrome: Checks if a string is the same when read forwards and backwards.
>> Concatenating Strings: Combines two strings end to end.
>> Finding the Occurrence of a Sub-string: Searches for a sub-string within a larger string.